      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WINDORAH (2) has been a little hard to follow, finishing out of the placings latest but was in winning form two back scoring in a Mix 6/7 at this track. Key player on best and worth another chance. GOBLIN (7) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 6th and beaten 4.5 lengths at this track (30.84). Has ability and is one of the better chances. CRACKERJACK HOPS (3) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (29.92) at Sandown behind Doongalla Serena in a Grade 5. Led around the bend before fighting on well and should give a sight. Winning chance. POINT MAN (5) is worth including after a top-three finish most recently.",
